data.name: RelativeDateTime_Format_DateTimeFormattingString_Override
data.comment: [Tag:DateTime.resx-odspnext] This controls the formatting of friendly datetime values when the date is more than a week in the past or future. The default value is the empty string. When empty, SharePoint will use RelativeDateTime_Format_DateTimeFormattingString to combine SharePoint's Month+Day format with the year. This is only appropriate when the language does not contain many different locale's with different formats. The other two options, "ShortDatePattern" and "LongDatePattern" use .NET to format the date. "ShortDatePattern" corresponds to the "d" format. "LongDatePattern" corresponds to the "D" format. See the .NET documentation for examples of what those patterns are for a given locale. Using a .NET pattern is recommended for languages which have different formatting rules depending on the locale, eg Arabic. Keep synced with string in strings.ress {Duplicate=match,strings;RelativeDateTime_Format_DateTimeFormattingString_Override} {ValidStrings="","LongDatePattern","ShortDatePattern"}{NoLocRule}
